  "response": "The oldest known written text is the Epic of Gilgamesh, which originates from ancient Mesopotamia (modern-day Iraq). The earliest surviving version of this epic poem dates back to around 2100 BCE, written in Sumerian cuneiform script on clay tablets. However, the story itself is believed to be even older, with oral traditions potentially dating back to around 2700 BCE. The epic tells the story of Gilgamesh, a legendary king of Uruk, and his adventures. While this is the oldest known complete written work, there are older written fragments and inscriptions that predate the Epic of Gilgamesh.",
